Employee Onboarding System - AWS Documentation
Project Overview
This project implements a secure Employee Onboarding System using AWS S3, AWS KMS, and AWS Secrets Manager. The application allows HR teams to onboard employees, upload documents, securely store credentials, and retrieve onboarding records through a Flask-based web interface.
Architecture
Frontend (HTML/JavaScript) -> Flask API -> AWS Services
• Amazon S3: Stores employee documents
• AWS KMS: Encrypts documents at rest using a Customer Managed Key (CMK)
• AWS Secrets Manager: Stores employee credentials securely

Workflow
1. User enters employee details and uploads Offer Letter, NDA and IT Policy.
2. Flask API receives the request.
3. Documents are uploaded to Amazon S3 using SSE-KMS encryption.
4. Temporary credentials are generated.
5. Credentials are stored in AWS Secrets Manager.
6. Employee records are displayed in the UI.
7. Credentials can be retrieved securely from Secrets Manager.
AWS Services Used
Amazon S3
- Stores onboarding documents.
- Documents organized by Employee ID folders.

AWS KMS
- Customer Managed Key (alias/onboarding-cmk).
- Used by S3 and Secrets Manager for encryption.

AWS Secrets Manager
- Stores employee credentials.
- Supports secure retrieval through API.
Code Components
app.py
- Flask web application.
- REST APIs for onboarding, listing employees, retrieving secrets and downloading documents.

onboard.py
- Core onboarding logic.
- KMS envelope encryption/decryption.
- S3 upload/download operations.
- Secrets Manager integration.
